                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1008">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bowen</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-04-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 30, 1902</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Bowen reports that the minister for foreign affairs, by order of the
                    President of Venezuela, has filed with him a strong protest <pb facs="1144"
                        n="1064" xml:id="pg_1064"/> against the act of the United States consul at
                    Port of Spain in clearing the <hi rend="italic">Viking</hi> for Caño Colorado,
                    characterizing it as an interference with Venezuelan commerce and an
                    infringement on Venezuelan sovereignty; that the minister states the incident is
                    serious and requests that his protest be forwarded to the Department of State at
                    Washington.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
